<section>
<!--<h5>The Challenge</h5>-->
<h2>You can't feel numbers.</h2>
<p>The feeling of hot air against the skin. The sight of storm clouds looming on the horizon. The weather isn't numbers and data. <b>It's a complex combination of sensory inputs.</b></p>

<p>Numbers effectively communicate precise data sets, but fail to convey the more nuanced sensations they represent. But paintings and other visual artifacts transcend the visual, transporting us to new realms of thought and feeling.</p>

<p class="emph">Can live weather data exist as a dynamic, visual system?</p>

</section>

