<section>
  <!--<h2>What I Learned</h2>-->
  <p class="emph left">Know what features are essential. Plan accordingly in the face of setbacks.</p>

  <p class="left">Although I was able to troubleshoot the text-masking issue, it cost me. I had less time to develop the interface of the project.</p>

  <p class="left">The experience of customizing the location could be better. What if it detected a user's location through Google's API? What if it took just a few less clicks to enter a location manually? What if a cookie stored the entered data for subsequent visits?</p>

  <p class="left">Maybe I could have ditched the temperature wave to tackle these problems, but I decided it was essential to the system. Overall, I feel I made the right decision, and plan to improve the usability in future iterations.</p>
